{
  "stem": "27340.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I was one of a member of a human chain that dealt with illegal immigration of survivors of concentration camps, from displaced persons camps as they were then called, not concentration camps anymore of course, who wanted to go to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The world was not interested in the remnants of concentration camps, those who had survived by guile, by luck, by anything else.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And the only opening that those people had, the only hope these people had was Palestine.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But Palestine was closed, as you know, because it was a British mandate, and the Brits had some responsibility towards the Arabs as well with regards to keeping immigration as-- as low in numbers as possible.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And so the only way to get into there was to get into there illegally.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "The Haganah, the forerunner of the Israel Defense Forces, was highly organized and very sophisticated with illegal immigration ships and so on and so forth.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But one had to get people down to the Mediterranean ports in France and in Italy from central Germany.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And the only way one could get them down was to march them down, literally.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "They went on foot.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And we, or my function together with many others, was to take responsibility of a certain sector within which, at nighttime when it was dark, we would be responsible to guide the group of 30 or 40 refugees and guide them along certain routes until in fact I handed over to a colleague of mine again.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "I in turn received them from a colleague of mine who was just one step further north, or further-- further east in geographical terms.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Ja, the-- the exact location I can't tell you because I don't remember it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's not a secret, but I just don't remember it.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
